HEADWORD: Olfaction
<hw>Ol*fac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Olfactory</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The sense by which
the impressions made on the olfactory organs by the odorous particles in
the atmosphere are perceived.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Olfactive</ent>⟦br⟧
